  <!--Paragraphs about game-->
  <div style="clear: both">
    <div class="pSubpage">
          <p class="pItem" style="text-align: center">
            <font class="mainTopics"> BACKGROUND INFORMATION </font> <br>
            Arcaea is a mobile rhythm game created by Lowiro. <br>
            Rhythm games are games that challenges a player's sense of rhythm <br>
            by making them tap notes to the beat according to a judgement line. <br>
            However, unlike other rhythm games, this game is 3-dimensional, <br>
            which makes for more difficult and challenging gameplay. <br>
            Currently, Arcaea is free to play, with some content locked behind a paywall. <br>
            Arcaea was released on March 9, 2017 on IOS and Android, and May 18, 2021 for Nintendo Switch.</p>
      
          <p class="pItem" style="text-align: center">
            <font class="mainTopics"> DIFFICULTIES, PERFORMANCE AND JUDGEMENT </font> <br>
            In the game, there are currently 4 difficulties, with one of them <br>
            requiring special methods to be unlocked. These difficulties are <font style="color: cyan">PAST</font>, <font style="color:lime">PRESENT</font>, <font style="color: purple">FUTURE</font>, and <font style="color:red">BEYOND</font>, <br> 
            each increasing in difficulty respectively. Your score determines your grade, which is determined by your performance. <br> 
            Scores are determined by the time you hit the notes when they reach the judgement line. <br> 
            For every note, you would get max points if you get a <font class="fontGradient1">◇PURE◇</font>, half points if you get a <font class="fontGradient2">◇FAR◇</font>, and no points if you get a <font class="fontGradient3">◇LOST◇</font>. <br> 
            Below are the score ranges and the grades you receive within that score range. </p>
    <!--Table showing the score ranges of each corresponding grade-->
    <table id="tableArcaea">
      <tr>
        <th>Grade</th>
        <th>Score Range</th>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>EX+</td>
        <td>9,900,000+</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>EX</td>
        <td>9,800,000 - 9,899,999</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>AA</td>
        <td>9,500,000 - 9,799,999</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>9,200,000 - 9,499,999</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>B</td>
