        <td>0 - 8,599,999</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
          <p class="pItem" style="text-align: center">
            <font class="mainTopics"> PARTNERS & RECOLLECTION GAUGES </font> <br>
            Currently, there are at least 50 partners in Arcaea (with more to come!), each having <br>
            a different type of recollection gauge.  Recollection Gauges are the bars you see on the left side of the screen when you <br> 
            play a song. There are partners with different RGs that make gameplay by means of increasing the recollection rate <br> 
            or reducing the damages of LOSTS (like Hikari or Winter Eto and Luna), or partners that make gameplay harder <br> 
            by means of making your recollection rate reduce significantly (like Zero Hikari, Tempest Tairitsu, or Fatalis Hikari). <br>
            The goal for partners with <font style="color: lime">EASY</font> or <font style="color: yellow">NORMAL</font> recollection gauges is to maintain your recollection rates equal or above 70. <br> 
            On the other hand, the goal for partners with <font style="color: red">HARD</font> recollection gauges is to maintain your recollection rates above 0.
            
          <p class="pItem" style="text-align: center">
          <font class="mainTopics"> TYPES OF NOTES </font> <br>
          Since this game is 3-dimensional, there are different notes other than what you normally expect in rhythm games. <br> 
            Floor notes appear on the floor and you must tap to hit them when it reaches the bottom judgement line to not get a LOST. <br> 
            Long notes are the same as floor notes, except you must hold them when it reaches the bottom judgement line and release when it ends. <br> 
            Sky notes are the same as floor notes, except they can be found anywhere within the top judgement line and the bottom judgement line. <br> 
            You must tap to hit  when it reaches your playing area. <br> 
            Arc notes are the same as long notes, except they can move up and down, and also left and right. <br> 
            <font style="color: cyan"> Blue arcs </font>must be hit with your left hand and <font style="color: magenta"> pink arcs </font> must be hit with your right hand. <br> 
            Traces have no contribution on gameplay, they are just there for decoration. <br> 
            Seen below are the 5 types of notes that can be seen in a chart in Arcaea. </p>
          <!--Different types of notes in Arcaea-->
          <table id="tableArcaea">  
            <tr>
