          <p class="pItem" style="text-align: center">
          <font class="mainTopics"> HOW TO UNLOCK </font> <br>
          There are a lot of songs that require very specific steps to unlock. Here are links to tutorials on how to unlock these. <br>
          <!--Links to tutorials to unlock specific songs-->
          <u><a href="https://youtu.be/7y0ns1bGrYI" target="_blank"> Grievous Lady </a> <br>
          <a href="https://youtu.be/jlT_5_SYw8s" target="_blank"> Fracture Ray </a> <br>
          <a href="https://youtu.be/1qYij3_KabU" target="_blank"> Tempestissimo </a> <br>
          <a href="https://youtu.be/jWm1xqO9qdU" target="_blank"> Every Song in Final Verdict </a> <br>
          <a href="https://youtu.be/8V6dSp1qkNM" target="_blank"> Every Song in Silent Answer </a> </u><br>
          To unlock songs with a difficulty of Beyond, you need a potential of at least 9.00 and you will need to go to World Mode to unlock them. </p>

          <p class="pItem" style="text-align: center">
          <font class="mainTopics"> TIPS & TRICKS </font> <br>
          It is MASSIVELY encouraged for you to play the Beginner and Advanced Tutorials first before diving in into the game, <br> 
          because this game has a concept that is way more different than any other rhythm game. <br>
          It is also important to fix your SETTINGS first (found in the top section of Arcaea's Music Play) <br>
          according to your liking, like the offset, or the notespeed (scrollspeed). This game is mainly compromised of <br>
          accuracy, precision, timing, speed, and readability. All of these would develop as you progress further or play more into the game. <br>
          To improve readability, I would recommend getting an app called <u><a href="https://apps.apple.com/us/app/sound-game-training/id1088874473" target="_blank">Sound Game Training</a></u> (currently only for IOS at the moment). <br> 
          Simply find a chart from YouTube and you can practice it according to how you like it! <br>
          Another thing I can suggest is finding hand cameras of people who have managed to Max PM charts if you are confused how to do some gameplay. <br>
          You also need good dexterity for this game because there are certain patterns like crossing your hands just to hit notes. <br> </p>

          <p class="pItem" style="text-align: center">
          <font class="mainTopics"> FUN FACTS </font> <br>
          <ul>
          <li>This game has collaborated with a lot of other rhythm games! Some of these include maimai, WACCA, Ongeki, and CHUNITHM.</li>
          <li>This game also hosted 2 song-making contests, with 1 of them ongoing right now!</li>
          <li>Currently, there are 9 known charters who have charted all of the songs in Arcaea. Some notable ones are Toaster, Nitro, and Exschwashion.</li>
          <li>As of writing this, there are currently 289 songs in Arcaea! (+2 if including Last | Eternity and Last | Moment)</li>
          <li>There is a chart called "dropdead", where the <font style="color: lime">Present</font>(9.5) difficulty has a higher difficulty than the <font style="color: purple">Future</font>(9.1) difficulty!</li>
          <li>The highest difficulty at the moment is <font style="color: red">Beyond 12</font>, with the song being Testify!</li>
          <li>There are also April Fools Charts (celebrated on April 1st of every year), where the new charts during that day break some of Arcaea's normal mechanics, like out-of-bound notes!</li>
          <li>Similarly, the <font style="color: red">Beyond</font> difficulties break some of Arcaea's normal mechanics, like extended playing field, and the increasing of 4 lanes of gameplay to 6! (this can exclusively be found in the Final Verdict pack)</li>
          <li>You can add Hikari and Tairitsu as friends with the Friend IDs of 000 000 001 and 000 000 002 respectively!</li>
          <li>Arcaea can be played with different handstyles, like thumb gameplay, index gameplay, or multifinger gameplay!</li>
          </ul></p>
